node.text:
Organizing for Kids 
.
Tired or overwhelmed with chores unending from the clutter of your kids/wards? Consider the following tips:
.
Limit toys: Children can never have enough toys. Let them keep a limit. When they get a new toy, they can give out an old one. 
.
Everything in its place: Teach your kids to put their belongings in the right place.
.
Use checklists:  A list of chores to be completed daily. Remember to keep it simple so they don’t get overwhelmed.
.
Be a good example and don’t hold back compliments/rewards as they progress and get better.
.
Integrate these guidelines into their daily lives and also remember that habits are built over time with patience.
.
.

A government official in the Philippines is to be removed from his post after being caught having sex with his secretary during a Zoom call.

Captain Jesus Estil, of the Fatima Dos village council in the province of Cavite, appeared not to know his camera was on at the time of the incident, witnessed by numerous members of the council’s staff.

Footage shows Estil and a woman stood a distance back from the camera in one window of a conference call. The call was reportedly part of a regular council meeting that took place on August 26.

The woman appears to begin to drop her trousers before Estil approaches the camera and seemingly attempts to turn it off. He is then seen walking away from the computer and back towards the woman.

As others continue the conference call, the pair can be seen having sex on the far side of the room.

After a number of minutes, Estil is seen walking back across the room while pulling up his trousers to rejoin the call.

The woman in the clip reportedly works for Estil as a secretary and also does the accounting of the local government’s office.

The scene was recorded by a staff member who was on the call.

After the video was made public, some residents of the village filed a petition to oust the captain for misconduct.

The Department of Interior and Local Government said that Estil will be relieved of his post as quickly as possible.

DILG Barangay Affairs Summons and Complains Chief Richard Geronimo said: “This is not simple misconduct, but grave misconduct.

node.text:
Caught the @netflix original "Desperados" last night.

Look, there's a lot happening in this one, much of it random (like Heather Graham's afterthought of a role), unoriginal, and fully predictable. 

But somehow also watchable.

Netflix's original content is basically trash 98% of the time. But if you like Hallmark or Lifetime romcoms & wish they were dialed up a single little notch, then you'll like this.

Always nice to see @nasimpedrad & @lamorne team up, they have great chemistry & seem to genuinely enjoy each other, which comes across on screen. I love @therealannacamp & was thrilled to see her here along with @sarahburnsme 

It takes you nowhere new, but if you want to take a familiar ride, to a tried & true destination, "Desperados" might just be the weekend watch for you.

5/10.

.

node.text:
Sibling Rivalry! Once we have spent a bit of time reflecting our kid’s feelings, we can try to move them towards resolving the conflict. We can gently suggest that they think of solutions on how to get along.#growingup #momlife #family #motherhood #siblings #siblinglove #momsofinstagram #motherhoodunplugged #mom #lifecoach #quarantinelife #quarantine #tuckeredout #troublemakers #mamasboys #siblinggoals #consciousparenting #positiveparenting #parentingtips #hoomans #furbrother #snugglesfordays #socialdistancingfail

We can say: “Trying to figure out how to share a toy can be difficult. Do you have any ideas that might work?”

“What can you guys do to fix this problem?”

“Are you guys ready to think of some solutions on who is going to sweep the floor or are you still too mad?”

What do you do if the kids don’t want to offer any solutions?

Go back to reflecting feelings, then name the problem and offer some suggestions with a neutral tone:

“Two children and one toy! It is tough to share! Do you want to hear what some other kids do? Some decide to take turns, each person taking five minutes each.. .Some kids decide to find other toys to play with…”

“This is tough one, two kids who don't want to sweep the floor and one mom who needs it to get done. Can I offer some suggestions that might work for you? Ben you do half the floor and Eli you do the other half…How about Eli you do it today and Ben you do it tomorrow…?”

We also need to remember that parenting is a slow process. You are setting the stage for how they will handle conflict later as they grow. They might not come up with solutions right now in this situation, but you are building a problem solving mindset.

And I knew you'd come back to me
You'd come back to me
And you'd come back to me
And you'd come back

And when I felt like I was an old cardigan

SO EASY FLATBREAD FOR WRAPS

This basic recipe makes a flatbread that best resembles a paratha x pita with slightly crispy edges and a soft centre that’s perfect for wraps. You can even roll it out thinner and make pita chips for dipping! There are only a few ingredients you’ll need for this recipe and it is so simple and straight forward that you’ll never buy store-bought wraps ever again! You don’t even need to turn on the oven or proof the dough.

Full recipe here: https://polyphagicabby.com/2020/08/19/so-easy-flatbread-for-wraps/

“Don’t let someone dim your light ... simply because it’s shining in their eyes”- (don’t remember the author’s name )üôè

Still smiling (and squinting) behind all the hate üòÇ I get nasty comments in person and online a lot of the time. Sometimes people say it’s “a joke”, other times, they really mean it - and honestly, it hurts at times. But after a long time of experiencing these (inevitable) comments, I’ve learnt to filter out the actual constructive criticism from the rubbish ‚ù§Ô∏è

When I’m feeling down about these sort of things I always read a quote by Gandhiji; he said that “Never apologize for being correct, or for being years ahead of your time. If you're right and you know it, speak your mind. Speak your mind. Even if you are a minority of one, the truth is still the truth.” Never be afraid to speak up and take a stand; to amplify the voices of communities that are oppressed and marginalised ‚úä

Also, I really feel the block function on Instagram is so underrated ü§£ It’s so important to fill our feed with content that makes us happy, feel good about ourselves, confident, inspired, laugh etc. Unfollow or block the accounts that don’t! I did this a few months ago and now going onto social media and seeing content that I love makes my day so much better ü§©

Don’t judge those who try to bring you down - we don’t know what they’re going through or where they’re coming from. Just remember that you are extraordinary in so many different ways and that “the truth is still the truth” (Gandhi) ‚ú®

We made these illustrated player tiles because we were tired of premade symbols that boxed us in. If your Druid doesn’t touch a scythe, if you’re playing with two Fighters, if you’re double classing... you know the problem that I’m talking about!

Choose from a set of 16 class tokens or 30 with classes + generic illustrations. The versatility will allow you to designate players appropriately and still have the freedom to use the same pieces for future games to come.

node.text: Emotional support are not service animals under the ADA. Service animals are animals that preform a life saving task or a task to help there handler in every day life do something that the handler other wise can’t do on there own. Service animals ethically should be 2-3 years of age to begging work and at least know 1 task before allowed public access in non pet friendly places. Service animals don’t have paper work or ID with in the untied states. Currently only mini horses and dogs are legally recognized as service animals by the ADA however please check with your state as different states may allow ( cats and monkeys). Service animals can not bark, pee/poop, lung, or be aggressive. They must be kept out of the way and ignored by the general public. They are not allowed in shopping carts or on tables as it a health code violation. Bringing in your pet risks the health and safety of your self and your dog and actual service handlers.
